If you are wondering what the trail conditions were like....this is a nice section a couple miles in. That's a ptarmigan in the middle. :) 4x4s can actually drive all the way to the bus...is that cheating?

Bus 142, aka the magic bus, and 2 others were pulled in by Yutan Construction in the 1960s using a D8 Cat. The others were removed but Bus 142 was left on Stampede Road with the purpose to serve as a shelter for hikers and hunters.
The trail to the magic bus is really an old road...it's not the most scenic but there is an occasional gem...I would guess this pond is about 7miles in
